name: Green Bean Salad with Feta Cheese
author: AHinojosa
summary: This green bean salad is a summer salad or side dish idea.
ingredients: ½ cup thinly sliced red onion
salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste
½ cup balsamic vinaigrette salad dressing
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Place walnuts on a baking sheet
Bake in preheated oven until toasted, 5 to 7 minutes
Remove from the oven and let cool, about 10 minutes
While walnuts cool, bring a large pot of water to a boil
Add green beans and cook, 5 to 7 minutes
Drain and rinse with cold water; drain again
Transfer green beans and walnuts to a mixing bowl and add feta, red onion, cranberries, salt, and pepper; gently toss together
